<section class="process section" id="process">
  <div class="shell">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal" style="color:#555">04 — How I build</p>
    <h2 class="process-heading reveal">Process that <em>ships.</em></h2>

    <div class="process-steps">
      <div class="process-step reveal d1">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <span class="process-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        <h3>Discover</h3>
        <p>Understand the business problem before touching code. Stakeholder context, user flows, technical audit—no building until the problem is clear.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step reveal d2">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <span class="process-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        <h3>Define</h3>
        <p>Clear spec, agreed constraints, prioritised scope. No ambiguity when build starts—only well-understood trade-offs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step reveal d3">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <span class="process-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        <h3>Build</h3>
        <p>Full-stack execution—frontend, backend, mobile, integrations. Shipped in iterations, not big bangs. Every decision justified.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step reveal d4">
        <div class="step-num">04</div>
        <span class="process-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        <h3>Ship</h3>
        <p>Production deployment, performance audit, monitoring in place. Launch is the start of the product, not the finish line.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step reveal d5">
        <div class="step-num">05</div>
        <span class="process-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        <h3>Iterate</h3>
        <p>Post-launch analytics, feedback loops, continuous improvement. Real products evolve—so does the engineering behind them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
